Remove first index of every string item and add that string to the given array.
for example: input - ["acd", "bcc", "aca"]  output - ["acd", "bcc", "aca", "aba"]

fun main(){
  val inputArray = arrayOf("acd", "bcc", "aca")
  val firstIndexValues = inputArray.map{it.first()}
  val resultArray = inputArray + firstIndexValues.joinToString("")
  println(resultArray.joinToString(","))
}

Above program is used minimum lines to complete the code.

